{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0168WQ8mF9jCyMihjindLhow","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Pn7igtXoWqcjLfKfqZSDMG","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lentil Walnut Soup.generated.21.txt","content":"LENTIL WALNUT SOUP\n\nThis hearty soup combines the earthiness of lentils with the rich\nnuttiness of walnuts, creating a deeply satisfying dish perfect for\ncold autumn evenings. The soup is naturally vegan and protein-rich,\nmaking it ideal for both health-conscious diners and those seeking\ncomfort food. Traditionally served with crusty bread and a drizzle\nof walnut oil for extra flavor.\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 cups dried lentils\n- 1 cup walnuts, roughly chopped\n- 2 large carrots, diced\n- 3 celery stalks, diced\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 liters vegetable broth\n- 2 tbsp olive oil\n- 1 tsp cumin\n- 1 tsp smoked paprika\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- Fresh thyme sprigs\n\nMethod:\nHeat oil in large pot. Sauté onion, carrots, celery, and garlic\nuntil tender, approximately 8 minutes. Add lentils, walnuts, and\nspices. Pour in broth and bring to boil. Reduce heat, simmer 40\nminutes until lentils are soft and creamy. Season with salt and\npepper. Serve hot with crusty bread and fresh thyme garnish."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":64866,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":64866},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c22f6373-1768-4fe9-8dfb-d92d5ab5fdd9","uuid":"0e31bd44-5985-43c9-a0c2-b221e3aceec0"}
