{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y3EbbgX6zKz31y1jTWg4mL","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Tomato Basil Pasta.generated.21.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c22f6373-1768-4fe9-8dfb-d92d5ab5fdd9","uuid":"7efe13eb-ee4c-4710-becc-d0084032d174","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Tomato Basil Pasta.generated.21.txt","content":"Page 14\n\nTOMATO BASIL PASTA\n\nIngredients:\n- 400g spaghetti or linguine\n- 800g canned tomatoes (or 1kg fres-\n  h tomatoes, chopped)\n- 1/2 cup fresh basil, roughly chopped\n- 6 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/4 cup extra virgin olive oil\n- 1 onion, diced\n- 1 tsp sugar\n- Salt and black pepper\n- Parmesan cheese for serving\n\nMethod:\nHeat olive oil in large pan over medium heat. Sauté garlic and onion\nuntil fragrant, about 3 minutes. Add tomatoes, breaking them up as\nthey cook. Simmer for 20-25 minutes, season with salt, pepper, and\nsugar. Meanwhile, cook pasta in salted boiling water until al dente.\nReserve 1 cup pasta water. Drain pasta and add to tomato sauce with\nbasil, tossing gently. Add pasta water as needed for desired\nconsistency. Top with Parmesan and fresh basil, serve immediately.","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
