{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014gqWAFVWCLaoEGz5N5ZwHL","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Herb Roasted Chicken Thighs.generated.21.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c22f6373-1768-4fe9-8dfb-d92d5ab5fdd9","uuid":"35fd793a-76ef-4108-a618-2e891018678c","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Herb Roasted Chicken Thighs.generated.21.txt","content":"HERB ROASTED CHICKEN THIGHS\n\nNothing quite compares to the aroma of herbs and roasting chicken\nfilling your kitchen on a lazy Sunday afternoon. This classic\npreparation brings out the natural flavors of the poultry while the\nherbs create a fragrant crust. The thighs remain incredibly moist\nduring cooking, making this an ideal dish for beginners. Serve with\nroasted vegetables and crisp white wine for a complete meal.\n\nIngredients:\n- 8 chicken thighs (bone-in, skin-on)\n- 4 tbsp olive oil\n- 6 fresh thyme sprigs\n- 4 fresh rosemary sprigs\n- 4 bay leaves\n- 8 cloves garlic, smashed\n- 2 lemons, halved\n- 1 tsp sea salt\n- Black pepper\n- 1/2 cup chicken broth\n- 1 tbsp balsamic vinegar\n\nMethod:\nPreheat oven to 425°F. Arrange thighs skin-side up in roasting pan.\nRub with oil, salt, pepper. Distribute herbs, garlic, and lemon\naround thighs. Pour broth around (not over) thighs. Roast 40-45\nminutes until skin is golden and internal temperature reaches 165°F.\nDrizzle with balsamic. Rest 5 minutes before serving with pan juices.","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
